  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife and add them to a pot with a lid with your <strong>basmati rice</strong>, 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>cardamom rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681316871346-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681316871346-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681316871346-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681316871346-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681316871346-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a very generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681316875055-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681316875055-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681316875055-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681316875055-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681316875055-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice 1/3 of your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds and finely chop the rest</p><p>Tip: Not a fan of spice? Remove the seeds!</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681316879045-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681316879045-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681316879045-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681316879045-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1681316879045-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required)</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong>,<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681316882855-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681316882855-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681316882855-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681316882855-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1681316882855-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the<strong> chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once starting to soften, add your<strong> garam masala</strong> to the pan with your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)<strong> </strong>and<strong> ground turmeric</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for 1-2 min</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1681316888473-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1681316888473-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1681316888473-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1681316888473-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1681316888473-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until the sauce is slightly thickened</p><p>Once slightly thickened, add the <strong>chopped green beans </strong>and cook, covered, for 3-4 min or until the beans are almost tender</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1681316892990-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1681316892990-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1681316892990-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1681316892990-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1681316892990-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the beans are almost tender, drain your<strong> king prawns</strong>, then add them to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 4-5 min or until the prawns are cooked through – this is your<strong> spicy king</strong> <strong>prawn madras curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1681316896753-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1681316896753-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1681316896753-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1681316896753-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1681316896753-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> spicy king prawn madras curry</strong> over the<strong> cardamom rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> reserved chilli rounds </strong>(can’t handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Tip: Watch out for any cardamom pods!</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
